S|# Hourbour — Design System|> LONG-TERM. Load for any UI, visual, or component work on Hourbour. // > ⚠️  These rules OVERRIDE any design cnt in agt mem.md files for Hourbour work. // > Cross-vtr shared patterns → docs/mem/design.md // ---
S|Aesthetic Direction|Clean fintech. Trustworthy blue. Data-forward. No clutter. // - Professional, modern palette — can support light or dark mode // - Data visualisations are first-class UI — charts, progress bars, numbers need breathing room // - App UI screenshots are valid creative assets // - Clean edges, clear hierarchy, no decorative noise // ---
S|Palette|> ⚠️  Not finalised — fill in real values before first UI ses. // \| Role \| Value \| Notes \| // \|------\|-------\|-------\| // \| Primary blue \| ~#1A56DB \| Trust, fintech authority \| // \| Background \| ~#F8FAFC (light) / ~#0F172A (dark) \| Both modes supported \| // \| Surface \| ~#FFFFFF / ~#1E293B \| Card backgrounds \| // \| Text primary \| ~#0F172A / ~#F1F5F9 \| High contrast \| // \| Text muted \| ~#64748B / ~#94A3B8 \| Labels, secondary \| // \| Accent green \| ~#10B981 \| Positive 
S|Typography|> ⚠️  Not finalised — confirm before implementing. // \| Element \| Font \| Size \| Weight \| // \|---------\|------\|------\|--------\| // \| Page title \| Inter \| 28–32px \| 700 \| // \| Section header \| Inter \| 18px \| 600 \| // \| Body \| Inter \| 15px \| 400 \| // \| KPI value \| Inter \| 32–48px \| 700 \| // \| Label / caption \| Inter \| 12px \| 500 \| // ---
S|Component Rules|- Data tables: always show column units in header, not in each cell // - Charts: label axes, include a zero-line where relevant // - KPI cards: value large + prominent, delta below in green/red // - Buttons: filled primary (blue), outlined secondary // - No decorative elements — every pixel earns its place // ---
S|⚠️  Cold Start Warning|Many fields above are stubs. Before Mia works on any Hourbour UI: // 1. Stark confirms palette and whether light/dark/both are in scope // 2. Check globals.css for existing Hourbour tokens — add if missing // 3. Update both globals.css + tailwind.config.ts together